NetWatch is a lightweight Python-based desktop application designed to monitor network performance in real time. It provides users with critical insights into download/upload speeds, latency, and more, with an easy-to-read graph and user-friendly interface.

Features
Real-time Network Statistics:
View live download and upload speeds in Mbps.
Monitor network latency in milliseconds.
Performance Graph:
Displays real-time trends for network performance.
Ping Utility:
Manually ping a user-specified server or website and view the response time.
Customizable Settings:
A dedicated panel for additional features and tools.
Requirements
Python 3.6+
Libraries:
PySide6
matplotlib
ping3
psutil
